## Whats up subtitle

This post demonstrates loading a Plotly chart definition (`data`, `layout`, optional `config`) from Hetzner Object Storage and rendering it directly inside MDX.

<PlotlyFromJson
    host="nbg1.your-objectstorage.com"
	bucket="public-plots"
	filepath="blog-sportsdata-art-activity-counts-bar-merged.json"
	height="520px"
	    notes={[
      "Source: CBS open data, 2025 snapshot.",
      "Values normalized per 100k inhabitants."
    ]}
/>

If the chart does not render, confirm that your object is publicly readable and your bucket CORS allows browser `GET` requests from your site domain.
